grab_ci <- function(model, vars) {
  ct <- fixest::coeftable(model)
  out <- tibble(
    variable  = rownames(ct),
    estimate  = ct[, 1],
    std.error = ct[, 2]
  ) %>%
    filter(variable %in% vars) %>%
    mutate(
      lb = estimate - 1.96 * std.error,
      ub = estimate + 1.96 * std.error,
      model = deparse(substitute(model))
    )
  out
}

collect_est <- function(mod) {
  est <- mod$est.avg
  est.out <- matrix(NA, nrow=1, ncol=7)
  est.out[1,1:7] <- est[1:7]
  colnames(est.out) <- c("estimate","se","lb","ub","se.boot","lb.boot","ub.boot")
  return(est.out)
}

make_panel_single <- function(df, facet_title,
                              ylab = NULL, xlab = NULL,
                              ylim_all = NULL,
                              show_ylim = TRUE) {
  df <- df %>% mutate(type = facet_title)

  p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = x_lab, y = estimate,
                      colour = ifelse(lb < 0 & ub > 0, "red", "black"))) +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed",
               colour = "grey60", linewidth = 0.9) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lb, ymax = ub),
                  width = 0.2, linewidth = 0.9, show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_point(size = 2) +
    scale_colour_identity() +
    facet_wrap(~type) +
    labs(x = xlab, y = ylab) +
    theme_bw() +
    theme(
      strip.background = element_rect(fill = "grey90", colour = "black"),
      strip.text       = element_text(size = 11, face = "bold"),
      axis.text.x      = element_text(size = 10,  hjust = 0.5),
      axis.title.x     = element_text(size = 11),
      axis.title.y     = element_text(size = 12)
    )

  if (show_ylim && !is.null(ylim_all)) {
    p <- p +
      scale_y_continuous(limits = ylim_all,
                         expand = expansion(mult = 0),
                         oob = scales::oob_keep)
  } else if (!show_ylim) {
    p <- p +
      scale_y_continuous(limits = ylim_all,
                         breaks = NULL, labels = NULL,
                         expand = expansion(mult = 0),
                         oob = scales::oob_keep) +
      theme(axis.text.y  = element_blank(),
            axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
            axis.title.y = element_blank())
  }

  p
}

What the Final Warning Means

F-test Failed. The estimated covariance matrix is singular.

This means:

When testing whether adding more latent factors significantly improves model fit, the statistical test could not be computed.

The covariance matrix was singular likely because there is insufficient variation or too many fixed effects relative to observations, or the added factors are collinear.

make_panel_single <- function(df, facet_title,
                              ylab = NULL, xlab = NULL,
                              ylim_all = NULL,
                              show_ylim = TRUE) {
  df <- df %>% mutate(type = facet_title)
  
  # Reorder x_lab by string length (shortest to longest)
  df <- df %>%
    mutate(x_lab = fct_reorder(x_lab, str_length(x_lab)))
  
  p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = x_lab, y = estimate,
                      colour = ifelse(lb < 0 & ub > 0, "red", "black"))) +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed",
               colour = "grey60", linewidth = 0.9) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lb, ymax = ub),
                  width = 0.2, linewidth = 0.9, show.legend = FALSE) +
    geom_point(size = 2) +
    scale_colour_identity() +
    facet_wrap(~type) +
    labs(x = xlab, y = ylab) +
    theme_bw() +
    theme(
      strip.background = element_rect(fill = "grey90", colour = "black"),
      strip.text       = element_text(size = 11, face = "bold"),
      axis.text.x      = element_text(size = 10,  hjust = 0.5),
      axis.title.x     = element_text(size = 11),
      axis.title.y     = element_text(size = 12)
    )

  #  Apply y-limits if provided
  if (show_ylim && !is.null(ylim_all)) {
    p <- p + coord_cartesian(ylim = ylim_all)
    # Or use: p <- p + lims(y = ylim_all)
  }
  
  return(p)
}

wtax | War Tax: tax revenues specifically earmarked for the war effort. |

# Function to count overlap
count_overlap <- function(start, end, crisis_years) {
  sum(crisis_years >= start & crisis_years <= end, na.rm = TRUE)
}

## Financial crisis 
GCD <- read.csv("../data/GCD/20160923_global_crisis_data.csv")

# From GCD: keep only selected variables, impute 0 for NAs. Create a binary indicator for any types of financial crisis,
GCD_sel <- GCD %>%
  # First filter to desired time range
  transmute(
    iso3 = CC3,
    year = Year,
    banking_crisis   = as.integer(if_else(Banking.Crisis   %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L)),
    systemic_crisis  = as.integer(if_else(Systemic.Crisis  %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L)),
    gold_standard    = as.integer(if_else(Gold.Standard    %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L)),
    domestic_default = as.integer(if_else(Domestic_Debt_In_Default %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L)),
    independence     = as.integer(if_else(Independence     %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L)),
    currency_crisis  = as.integer(if_else(Currency.Crises  %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L)),
    inflation_crisis = as.integer(if_else(Inflation.Crises %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L)),
    external_default = as.integer(if_else(SOVEREIGN.EXTERNAL.DEBT.2..DEFAULT.and.RESTRUCTURINGS..1800.2012..Does.not.include.defaults.on.WWI.debt.to.United.States.and.United.Kingdom.but.includes.post.1975.defaults.on.Official.External.Creditors %in% c("1", 1), 1L, 0L))
  ) %>%
  mutate(any_crisis = as.integer(
    banking_crisis + systemic_crisis + currency_crisis + inflation_crisis + external_default + domestic_default > 0
  ))
# 1. Prepare crisis years per country (keeping the crisis flag!)
GCD_crisis <- GCD_sel %>%
    filter(any_crisis == TRUE) %>%
    select(iso3, year, any_crisis)

# 2. Expand and join as before
ccwp_expanded <- ccwp %>%
    rowwise() %>%
    mutate(year = list(seq(yrbeg1, yrend1))) %>%
    unnest(year)

ccwp_overlap <- ccwp_expanded %>%
    left_join(GCD_crisis, by = c("stateabb" = "iso3", "year" = "year")) %>%
    group_by(WAR, statenum, stateabb, yrbeg1, yrend1) %>%
    summarise(overlap_domestic_crisis = sum(any_crisis, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop")

# 4. Join back to original ccwp
ccwp_war_3 <- ccwp_war_2 %>%
  left_join(ccwp_overlap, by = c("WAR", "statenum", "stateabb", "yrbeg1", "yrend1"))
lin_wtax_domestic_crises    <- feols(wtax     ~ overlap_domestic_crisis + duration,    data = ccwp_war_3, cluster = "stateabb")
## NOTE: 30 observations removed because of NA values (LHS: 30).
lin_domtax_domestic_crises  <- feols(domtax   ~ overlap_domestic_crisis + duration,    data = ccwp_war_3, cluster = "stateabb")
## NOTE: 26 observations removed because of NA values (LHS: 26).
lin_domwf_domestic_crises   <- feols(domwf    ~ overlap_domestic_crisis + duration,    data = ccwp_war_3, cluster = "stateabb")
## NOTE: 10 observations removed because of NA values (LHS: 10).
lin_mnyabrd_domestic_crises <- feols(mnyabrd  ~ overlap_domestic_crisis + duration,    data = ccwp_war_3, cluster = "stateabb")
## NOTE: 12 observations removed because of NA values (LHS: 12).
lin_totalbrw_domestic_crises<- feols(totalbrw ~ overlap_domestic_crisis + duration,    data = ccwp_war_3, cluster = "stateabb")
## NOTE: 17 observations removed because of NA values (LHS: 17).
ci_domestic_crises1   <- grab_ci(lin_wtax_domestic_crises, "overlap_domestic_crisis")
ci_domestic_crises2  <- grab_ci(lin_domtax_domestic_crises, "overlap_domestic_crisis")
ci_domestic_crises3  <- grab_ci(lin_domwf_domestic_crises, "overlap_domestic_crisis")
ci_domestic_crises4  <- grab_ci(lin_mnyabrd_domestic_crises, "overlap_domestic_crisis")
ci_domestic_crises5  <- grab_ci(lin_totalbrw_domestic_crises, "overlap_domestic_crisis")

df <- merged_use_panel_2 %>%
  arrange(iso3, year) %>%
  group_by(iso3) %>%
  mutate(
    war_onset = as.integer(at_war == 1 & dplyr::lag(at_war, default = 0) == 0),
    in_default = as.integer(external_default == 1),
    default_start = as.integer(in_default == 1 & dplyr::lag(in_default, default = 0) == 0),
    default_spell_id = cumsum(default_start),
    dur_default = ifelse(in_default==1, ave(in_default, iso3, default_spell_id, FUN = cumsum), 0L)
  ) %>% ungroup()


df <- df %>%
  mutate(dur_default = ifelse(is.na(dur_default), 0L, dur_default))

# cloglog link approximates continuous-time hazard; include year FE as baseline hazard
m1 <- feglm(
  war_onset ~ in_default + poly(dur_default, 2) +  any_crisis | iso3 + year,
  data = df, family = binomial("cloglog"), cluster = "iso3"

w <- 10L  # post-war window length
df2 <- merged_use_panel %>%
  arrange(iso3, year) %>%
  group_by(iso3) %>%
  mutate(
    # mark war end: last year of a war spell
    war_end = ifelse(at_war == 1 & lead(at_war, default = 0) == 0, year, NA_integer_),

    # carry last war_end forward so each year knows most recent war
    war_end = zoo::na.locf(war_end, na.rm = FALSE, fromLast = TRUE),

    # event time relative to war_end
    tau = year - war_end,

    # post-war window indicator
    postwar = as.integer(tau >= 0 & tau <= w),

    # duration of current war spell (reset to 0 when not at war)
    spell_id = cumsum(at_war == 1 & lag(at_war, default = 0) == 0),
    war_dur_in_spell = ifelse(at_war == 1,
                              ave(at_war, spell_id, FUN = cumsum),
                              0),

    # outcome: in external default
    y_default = as.integer(external_default == 1)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

    defaults_postwar = sum(y_default == 1 & postwar == 1, na.rm = TRUE),
    defaults_at_war  = sum(y_default == 1 & at_war == 1, na.rm = TRUE),
    defaults_peace   = sum(y_default == 1 & at_war == 0 & postwar == 0, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()  # Always good practice

Prolonged defaults often overlap with wars. You have 208 years where a country is in war and in default, and 70 years in your postwar window that also coincide with default.

But defaults also occur outside wars. There are 1093 peace years with default thats the majority of defaults. So being in default doesnt guarantee war.

The postwar coding is overlapping with war. Notice how postwar=1 rows never coincide with at_war=0. That suggests that your war_end assignment (via zoo::na.locf(fromLast=TRUE)) is carrying war ends forward while still inside war spells. As a result, postwar years are not truly after war, but overlapping with late-war years.
